               <head>Manuscript containing two works</head>
               <msContents class="#multipleWorks">
                  <summary>Manuscript containing two works</summary>
                  <msItem n="1" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105554" xml:id="Uk_Or_15666-item1">
                     <locus from="1v" to="31v">ff 1v-31v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_f7434">Munshī Ghulām Rasūl</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7434" type="supplied">منشی غلام رسول</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_22061">Persian primer</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Composed for a European, perhaps by one Munshī Ghulām Rasūl: see note on front flyleaf. This work comprises the following sections: Introduction to the alphabet; Conjugation of the Verb Amudun, to come; Infinitives of Verbs; Familiar Dialogues; Letters; Some words and Phrases of general use.</p>
                        <p> Other contents: front endpaper, note: ‘Dear Anderson / This Book is sent you / by your old Moonshee / Golaum Russool / Yours sincerely (?) / P (?) W Spottiswoode / 6 March 1796’. </p>
                        <p>Title supplied. </p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <filiation />
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem n="2" class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100076" xml:id="Uk_Or_15666-item2">
                     <locus from="32v" to="79v">ff 32v-79v</locus>
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="supplied" key="person_73859635">Saʻdī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_73859635" type="supplied">سعدی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20962">Gulistān</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_20962">گلستان</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Part of the classic work by Sa‘dī, here evidently intended to serve as an introduction to Persian literary prose style. Included in this manuscript are Bāb 1 and most of Bāb 2.</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" otherLangs="ara">Persian with quotations in Arabic. </textLang>
                     <filiation />
                  </msItem>
